  Locus:
    Page: 379
    Verse: 6
Tags:
  - Pride
---
There is perhaps not one of our natural passions so hard to subdue as
pride. Disguise it, struggle with it, stifle it, mortify it as much as
one pleases, it is still alive, and will everyn ow and then peep out and
show itself.
